// A terminal `jmp` to a label in another compilation unit must not emit a
// frame-restore SEP/REP between the body and the jmp instruction. The callee
// `ext_callee` declares `@a16 @i16` as its entry mode, and the caller enters
// that mode via `@a16 { ... }` immediately before the jmp. The lowering
// previously emitted a SEP #$20 here to "restore" the surrounding @a8 mode at
// the closing `}`, which broke the callee's declared contract. With the fix,
// no SEP is emitted, and execution transfers to ext_callee in the @a16/@i16
// mode the callee expects.

naked main @a8 @i8 {
    @a16 {
        lda #$0001
        jmp ext_callee
    }
}
